<h1>Accounts and Billing</h1>


<DIV align=center><STRONG><BR>Creating An Account</STRONG> </DIV>
<P><BR>Please make sure that you have your registration code and e-mail address ready before creating an account.</P>
<P align=left>After running the <EM>EverQuest</EM> executable and performing the patch process, you will be taken to the <EM>EverQuest</EM> front-end screen. Select "Account", then left-click on the "New Account" button, this will bring up the account registration screen. </P>
<OL>
<LI>Enter your name, address, e-mail address, and date of birth by left clicking in the field, then typing in the information. The TAB key may be used to move the cursor to the next field. Once all of the information on each registration screen has been filled out, click on the "Next" key located at the bottom right side of the screen.<BR><BR>
<LI>Enter your PC specifications and answer the other general interest questions. Please note that the PC and general interest questions are not required to create the account. After you have completed this section of the registration click the "Next" key to continue.<BR><BR>
<LI>Select a Chat Handle and enter your EverQuest account key. An account key is included with <EM>EverQuest</EM>. The login name that you select will be used to connect to the EverQuest servers, and will also be seen while you are in the <EM>EverQuest</EM> chat rooms.<BR><BR>
<LI>Enter your Sony Station login and password. If you do not have a current Sony Station account, you may create one by simply entering a desired login name and password. After selecting a Station name and password, left-click on the "Finish" button located at the bottom right side of the screen. <BR><BR>
<LI>You will then be required to enter your Station name and password, do so, then left-click on the "Connect" button. After you enter your Station name information, a window will appear asking you to subscribe. Left-click the "Now" button to begin a subscription. Select a method of payment and fill-in all required billing information, then left-click on the "Finish" button located at the bottom left side of the screen. Your billing information will then be processed; this may take a few minutes. After acceptance, you may want to sign up for the <STRONG><A href="http://www.station.sony.com/allaccess/">SOE All Access Plan</A></STRONG>, which includes <EM>EverQuest</EM> Online Adventures, PlanetSide, and The Station Pass games. Once accepted, you may then return to the front-end screen and select "Connect" to begin playing <EM>EverQuest</EM>.</LI></OL>
<P align=left>If you encounter any problems with the billing process, please e-mail The Station using an easy-to-use form from <A target=_blank href="http://www.station.sony.com/en/services/help/help.jsp">Account Services</A>. <BR></P><BR>
